div.p:
You might have walked where Jesus walked
     and stayed where he was staying;

You might have eaten bread and sop
     and knelt where he was praying;

He might have washed your weary feet
and wiped them with his dryer;

He might have laid his precious bands
     upon your head with Fire.

You might have eased his weary way
     and wiped away his bleeding;

You might have helped in his defense
     when he was sorely needing;

Most disappointing words are oft
     expressed by tongue and writing;

The saddest words, "It might have been"
     are always the most biting.
